  "model_paragraph": "The pictures show two simple home-made water filters. In both, unsanitary water is poured into two-litre bottles onto a layer of gravel, which filters out large pieces of dirt. The water then seeps down to a layer that consists of ground rocks or coarse sand. However, in the first filter the water passes through charcoal before a final layer of fine sand, whereas the order is reversed in the second. A further difference is that the first uses cloth while the second uses cotton balls at the base. In short, both filters clean water in practically the same way, with only slightly different final stages.",
